  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated MARPs HIV/AIDS Prevention Program (IMHIPP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HAI is implementing a program to provide HIV/AIDS prevention and support services to MARPs and their sexual partners in Nigeria through support from USAID &#x2013; PEPFAR.   IMHIPP strengthens the capacity of local MSM/LGBT organizations to deliver HIV/AIDS services, providing training to officially formalize them into independent NGOs recognized by the Government of Nigeria. The program prepares these NGOs to take over implementation of MSM programming throughout the country, while concurrently training peer educators to conduct outreach and promote HIV prevention awareness, supporting direct community-based medical services, and promoting an enabling policy environment.</narrative>
  </description>
